        rationale: "This nodule has multiple high-risk ultrasound features consistent with TI-RADS 5 (highly suspicious). Microcalcifications are the most specific feature for papillary thyroid cancer. The size (1.5 cm) exceeds the 1 cm threshold for FNA biopsy in TI-RADS 5 nodules. Since TSH is normal, thyroid scintigraphy is not needed."
