        rationale: "Follicular carcinoma is defined by capsular and/or vascular invasion, which can only be assessed on a histologic tissue section showing the relationship between the tumor and its capsule. FNA provides individual cells without tissue architecture. Therefore, Bethesda IV (follicular neoplasm) requires diagnostic lobectomy for definitive classification. Molecular testing (ThyroSeq) may help refine risk."
