      action: "Inhibits central COX enzymes, reducing prostaglandin synthesis in the CNS; provides analgesia and antipyresis without antiplatelet effects (does not increase bleeding risk — critical advantage over NSAIDs in post-tonsillectomy patients); does NOT have peripheral anti-inflammatory activity",
      sideEffects: "Hepatotoxicity (dose-dependent; max 75 mg/kg/day in children, not to exceed 4g/day; account for ALL sources including combination products); rare: rash, anaphylaxis",
